<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/heroclix/treports/treports.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/vs/treports/treports.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Texas Open: San Angelo<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10528'>Robert "Surge" Hendon</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10528&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 10, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Pre-Tourney<br />
<br />
After scrubbing out in Houston&#39;s Open. I knew I would have to play in the San Angelo one. So Friday rolls around and I still have no deck. I haven&#39;t really thought about one and am figuring I will put something together later on that night while playtesting with friends. Well I am fixing to head to the local cardshop, but it closed early so the storeowner could go to a concert. Oh well. So I meet up with my friends, Nathan and Conor and we head to my house to playtest. I build a deck while Nathan and Conor play and catch up on rules since neither has played in a tournament in at least a month. I put together a super fellowship w/toys deck with moria swarm as shadow just for cycling mainly. I play Nathan 2 games and win both. I then help Conor change his deck to a mirror/uruk side that I can&#39;t play cuz uruks hate me and screw me with the draws 9 times out of 10. So we end up getting 3 hours of sleep before we head on out to San Angelo. The ride there was pretty much boring stretch of highway, but I have not seen so many dead animals on the side of a road in my life.<br />
<br />
Tourney starts<br />
<br />
Me - Robert Hendon (1706)<br />
<br />
1st Game<br />
Ryan Manelick (1587) Boromir<br />
<br />
I win the bid 5 to 0. Start the wonder twins and pull wonder triplet. I know not original, but it wins. He starts Boromir. I don&#39;t know what to expect here as I have never seen someone just start the rare Boromir. This game is very eventful as he is playing moria archery while his fellowship I don&#39;t think got set up. I just move way ahead and am at 8 while he is at 6. He moves to seven, I play stuff and draw up rare Aragorn. For some reason he moves to 8. I play out my hand draw up a servant and a path to go with the path in my hand. I play Aragorn, move and he has 3 minions, but I doubt it would have matter much as Aragorn could take whatever he wanted, and 2 paths for Frodo protection. <br />
FW +3<br />
<br />
Well first game win is always good. Next up....<br />
<br />
2nd Game<br />
Nathan Friedman (1741) Dwarf superfellowship/Sauron tracker doublemove haters<br />
<br />
Great playing someone I drove with. Well we know what to expect mostly. I move to 3. He moves to 2. I play some basic moria set-up and drop enquea. He stops. I move to 4. He moves to 3 after dropping a 6th companion. I drop another enquea and kill of gimli. He stops and I move to 5. He moves to 4 after dropping another companion. Now here is where I basically win. I drop another enquea and kill gloin. I know that I can move one at a time and he won&#8217;t be able to keep up. I end up swarming him at site 5.<br />
<br />
I had an incredible draw there. 3 enqueas by site 4 sucks.<br />
<br />
3rd Game<br />
Giang Do (1718) aragorn/gandalf fellow/nazgul<br />
<br />
I win bid 5 to 0. Pull Sam and see aragorn, gandalf, Boromir in opening hand. I think he is running nazgul, but I don&#8217;t remember what he told me. So I just move. He drops blade tip, black breath and a nazgul. I breathe a sigh of relief. I feed Sam and let Arwen have black breath blade tip. He moves, nothing really stops for ford. I decide I am going to give him enough for 2 nazguls, might as well give him all I have. Drop Boromir, aragorn, gandalf, move and all he has is witchking. Another sigh of relief. Arwen eats it and aragorn takes a wound. We both basically move 1 site a turn until he moves past me to 6. Here I drop scavenger w/sci and guard commander. He puts Frodo w/sting on scavenger and gandalf on guard commander. He does Frodo first, paths, I sac armory and pump with commander and that is game. He then realizes the commander. I say yea he is a MVP, as no one really knows what he does. I am really the only one here that plays with 2. He is good in defeat and he is a really cool guy. He just made the mistake that everyone else makes and it cost him. I know we will play many more games if we can start to have some sanctioned tournaments here in Texas.<br />
<br />
Despite his mistake I think it would have been close as I was drawing 2 flaming brands next and probably would have been able to spot 5 minions to prevent him from moving. So I am 3-0 and looking good. Now we get lunch so me, Nathan, Conor, Giang and Tad go eat at blimpies cuz KFC was bankrupt. WTF is that? How does a franchise go bankrupt? I think I heard that the franchise owner was embezzling or some crap from the td. We get back and I find out I am one of 2 undefeated people. So next up....<br />
<br />
4th game<br />
Matt ? (?) Aragorn/gandalf/Moria<br />
<br />
I forgot his last name, but I don&#39;t remember seeing him ranked. We both just set-up and I move to 5 first and survive. He moves to 5 and I drop balrog and 3 other minions. He assigns one to aragorn, balrog to gandalf, and other 2 to Frodo. He paths, I sac to armories and then he says crap I wanted to exert aragorn to take on 3 minions. I say sorry but this is the open and I can&#39;t let you take it back. Normally I would, but it was a high lvl tournament and I didn&#8217;t want to lose now due to me being nice and I sure didn&#8217;t want to lose the tournament because of it. I still felt like a jack a** for it and still do. <br />
<br />
I still hate it when people make mistakes like that...<br />
<br />
5th game<br />
Conor Brace (1642) super fellowship mirror/uruks<br />
<br />
Well I built his deck so I know what to expect. I know to keep at 4 companions cuz of uruks, and he gets set-up early with mirror and I lose 3 amories by site 4. I have not drawn really anything worth a gosh darnit for minions or moria conditions. I don&#8217;t draw much for fellowship except companions to replace fallen comrades. Basically he moves to 9 with exhausted Boromir, legolas, gandalf, gp with 1 wound and Frodo. I put out a bunch of minions and get a moria scout with they are coming I just played and pulled a sci with relics and draw enquea. I have a troll in hand. I am 1 short to play both. If I would have gotten a runner instead of scout, I could have played both. I can&#8217;t really say if this is a mistake or not as you cant predict what you are going to draw. I do think though if I would have thought about it longer and saw I only had 1 enquea in discard pile, I would have played it differently, however now I have to wait to see if he assigns wrong. He doesn&#8217;t and I can&#8217;t pull out victory, as I couldn&#39;t overwhelm gandalf or Frodo as he had 2 paths, and the troll can only eat Boromir and gandalf. <br />
<br />
I was a little pissed off at the error. I haven&#39;t made a mistake in weeks and I can&#39;t really tell if that was a mistake. I would appreciate it if people would have done it differently out of all honesty.<br />
<br />
6th and final game<br />
Tad Conaty (1682) super fellowship/nazgul<br />
<br />
I go first yet again. Went first all 6 games. No one out bid 5. I start and his nazgul are slowing me down, as I don&#39;t see the flaming brands until he is at 8. So he is just running saccing guys and shooting them down. I have drawn terrible again shadow wise and in wrong order for fellowship. I know to stay with 5 companions in fear of enquea. I really don&#8217;t get set-up and when I do I move to 7 while he is at 8. He drops cantea and attea. I shoot cantea twice and for some reason let him assign the archery from legolas. He plays it right and kills cantea and I am stuck with 2 paths and rumil in my hand. I didn&#8217;t want to give him enough to drop more nazgul out of his hand. I have to discard rumil and hold on to the 2 paths. This is huge as I still have troll, enquea in my hand for site 9 and the only moria orc I draw is a flanker. I can&#8217;t drop troll/enquea for win yet again and the next 4 cards in order are sca/runner/sca/runner and I have an armory and relic out. If I had shot attea then I would have maybe won. I didn&#39;t look at his hand, though and he might have had it anyways.<br />
<br />
So after my sweet start I lose 2 games for same reason, just different ways of getting there. Conor loses to Spencer in his last game so Tad and Spencer duel it out for champ. Tad wins what is a really insane game. Both had their fellowships complete at site 2. Both were playing nazgul. So top 4 were 2 nazgul/moria/and an uruk. My only satisfaction out of it were the fact I had 2 decks in top 4 for once as I am not a good deck builder I find that satisfactory. If people would respond to the enquea question I would appreciate it, as I would like to have seen what people would do when you don&#8217;t know what you are going to draw. I think I would change it now and for some reason I didn&#8217;t. I think if given the option again without knowing what I would have drawn, I would play the runner. Extra twilight should always be better.<br />
<br />
Well for the props/slops<br />
<br />
Props<br />
<br />
Everyone that showed up.<br />
Jerry the td for running a smooth tournament<br />
Nathan for driving the boring trip.<br />
Conor for making 3rd after not playing in a month<br />
Tad for winning.<br />
Tad and Giang for driving 8 hours to play.<br />
<br />
Slops<br />
Ryan for dropping after 0-2 and hurting my strength of schedule enough to prevent 3rd.<br />
Ryan Christian for saying he was going to go and then not going.<br />
Alan and others from Houston that decided not to go when they could have had a ride.<br />
Anyone else I didn&#39;t mention for not showing up.<br />
Me for being somewhat retarded there and going 0-2 after 4-0.<br />
<br />
Well that is it. I guess I will have to do grinders now, unless someone can say when Oklahoma&#8217;s open is.<br />
<br />
Rob<br />
